original_title: Volunteer Jam: Starring The Charlie Daniels Band
overview: In 1975, The Charlie Daniels Band performed the second of their legendary Volunteer Jams at Middle Tennessee Statue University in Murfreesboro, Tennessee. This annual event featured a number of special guests, including The Marshall Tucker Band, Dickey Betts and Chuck Leavell from the Allman Brothers band, Jimmy Hall, Dru Lombar, Bill Hart & Gary Peacemaker.
tagline: The First Full-Length Southern Rock Motion Picture
title: Volunteer Jam: Starring The Charlie Daniels Band
